*------------------------------------------*
|  Compare thickness computation's methods |
*------------------------------------------*

Note : Sorry if you find language faults in this document, the author hasn't got a perfect 
english.

Usage :
-------

This programm compares the thickness distributions computed by :
  - the Shape Diameter Function method (SDF) ;
  - a volumetric method, with chosen resolutions ( for the convertion of the mesh ).
The result is saved in a gnuplot script you can run to create a PDF file, where you could
find the differents curves plotted.

More precisely, the programm uses CGAL tools to compute the SDF values, Binvox to voxelize
the mesh with the different resolutions, and MAEVA tools to compute the volumic thickness using
medial axis.


Needed :
--------

- Binvox ( http://www.cs.princeton.edu/~min/binvox/ )
- Cmake
- CGAL ( https://www.cgal.org/ )
- MAEVA Toolit install ( http://liris.cnrs.fr/david.coeurjolly/code/maeva.html )
- "raw2vol" executable in DGtalTools ( http://dgtal.org/tools/ )
-


How to compile :
----------------

Be careful
----------

In off2vol.sh, my path for raw2vol is : ~/Documents/logiciels/DGtalTools/build/converters/
raw2vol

Change this path by yours ( the part after DGtalTools must be the same as mine )


- volFillExterior
-----------------
$ cd volFillExterior
$ cd build
$ cmake ..
$ make

- main programm
---------------


$ cd ../../build
$ g++ -Wall compare_resol.cpp -o compare_resol
$ cmake ..
$ make

Start the programm :
--------------------

in the build repository,

$./profils path/to/the/.off/object.off path/to/the/resolutions/file.txt

example : with the resolutions.txt file included :

./profils ~/Documents/objects/object.off resolutions.txt  


	
